documents.content: Error: BigQuery job failed: Access denied to dataset prod-analytics Resolution: Added BigQuery Data Editor role to service account Context: Production data pipeline accessing analytics dataset
Error: Dataflow job timeout after 60 minutes in region us-central1 Resolution: Increased worker machine type from n1-standard-1 to n1-standard-4 Context: Large dataset processing during peak hours
Error: Cloud Storage upload failed: Insufficient permissions for bucket Resolution: Added Storage Object Creator role to service account Context: Daily backup job writing to storage bucket
Error: Pub/Sub subscription acknowledgment failed: quota exceeded Resolution: Requested quota increase and implemented message batching Context: High-volume message processing during traffic spike
Error: SQL query failed: table not found in dataset Resolution: Updated table name reference and verified schema Context: Analytics pipeline after table rename

Title: BigQuery Permission Issues Troubleshooting Description: Step-by-step guide for resolving BigQuery access denied errors Steps: 1. Identify service account used 2. Check current IAM roles 3. Add appropriate BigQuery roles 4. Test access 5. Monitor for 24 hours

Title: Dataflow Job Performance Optimization Description: Guide for optimizing slow or timing out Dataflow jobs Steps: 1. Check worker resource utilization 2. Analyze data skew patterns 3. Adjust machine types 4. Optimize windowing 5. Enable autoscaling
